http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/Another-visual-treat/article13993436.ece

A painting exhibition organised by the Kerala Lalithakala Akademi offered another visual treat at the venue of the International Theatre festival of Kerala.Speaking after inaugurating the exhibition, Akademi Chairman Soorya Krishnamoorthy said the theatre had a close association with painting. Paintings of around 20 artists have been displayed at the venue. The themes vary from challenges of the globalisation to protests against violation of human rights.The exhibition provides a visual treat for the people coming from various parts of the world to watch the plays at the festival.